parsed.audit_log: <AUDIT_LOG>PHASE 1: Candidate 3 (picked reasoning F) crystallizes to: remove top 6-row legend; decode each legend color C as TURN-LEFT if its bar is in the left interior column of its 6-wide panel else TURN-RIGHT; in the remaining board find the 8-seed’s bounding box (k×k in training), launch 4 identical k×k movers from the seed in N/S/E/W; each step attempts a 1-cell shift—if out-of-bounds then stop that mover; if the shift would overlap any non-background, non-8 obstacle color C then do not move and instead rotate direction 90° per C’s turn rule; otherwise move and paint all covered background cells to 8; output is the painted board (obstacles unchanged). Candidate 9 (picked reasoning B) crystallizes to: remove legend; draw only a vertical and horizontal k-thick 8 ‘cross’ from the seed to the nearest obstacles/bounds (no turning/bouncing), never overwriting obstacles. PHASE 2 (ground truth): Candidate 3 passes 3/3—Ex1 requires extra vertical stripe(s) and a bottom horizontal band (from turning at color-1/2/4) beyond a simple cross; Ex2 requires an extra stripe and a right-side band (from turning at color-3/6) beyond a cross; Ex3 requires multiple stripes plus large filled bands (from turns at color-3/4/2/6) that match the official output layout. Candidate 9 fails 3/3 because all official outputs contain additional turned segments/extra stripes/bands that cannot be produced by a single non-turning cross. PHASE 3 (test consistency): Candidate 3’s proposed 24×24 output is consistent with its mover+turn rule (k=3 here; the top band at rows 3–5 and the long lower band at rows 14–16 are exactly what the two turning events at colors 2 and 4 generate). Candidate 9’s test grid is consistent with its own cross rule but the rule is falsified by training.</AUDIT_LOG>

example_audit.summary: Matches the solved examples: legend-based left/right turn decoding + four seed-sized movers that paint 8 while turning on obstacles reproduces the extra stripes/bands seen in all three official outputs (which a simple cross cannot explain).

Treat the 8 seed’s bounding box as an H×W block; launch four copies moving U/D/L/R, painting background as 8, turning when the next step would overlap an obstacle color, and stopping at bounds; output is the union of painted trails.
